<h1>Forums</h1>

<p>WineHQ hosts several mailing lists for submitting patches, tracking CVS
commits, and discussing Wine. They are now handled by Mailman, feature a
very customizable user subscription config (digests, no mail, ...), and can
be subscribed to <a href="/mailman/listinfo">via WWW</a>
or by sending mail to <i>listname</i>-request@winehq.com with a subject line of
"subscribe". To unsubscribe, use a subject line of "unsubscribe
<i>password</i>" using the password you got when you subscribed,
or just use <a href="/mailman/listinfo">the Mailman web interface</a>.
You should be subscribed to the lists before you post to them, otherwise
your posting will be treated as possible spam by the mailing list software.
</p>
<p>
There are now two web archives. <a href="mailto:jfreed@johnfreed.com">John Freed</a>
runs the old one, going back to 1998, and the new hypermail
archives stores everything after October 2000.
</p>

