  <h4> Using procmail to filter mailing lists </h4>
Many people who
subscribe to high traffic lists prefer to have their software
prefilter list traffic into mailboxes. Here's an example of how to do
this with <a href="http://www.iki.fi/~era/procmail/">Procmail</a>.
First, install procmail. Second, put the following line in your
<code>.forward</code> file:
<pre>
"|/usr/bin/procmail"
</pre>
Finally, construct a <code>.procmailrc</code> file which suits your needs. 
Here is one which just sorts Wine mailing list mail into folders in the
<code>~/mail</code> directory:
<pre>
PATH=/bin:/usr/bin:/usr/bin
MAILDIR=$HOME/mail      #you'd better make sure it exists

:0:
* ^TOwine-devel
wine-devel

:0:
* ^TOwine-cvs
wine-cvs

:0:
* ^TOwine-patches
wine-patches
</pre>
